title: Frank Lloyd Wright Chevron Design Earrings
description: During Frank Lloyd Wright’s Prairie School period many variations of chevron designs are found. From the very palatial Dana House to the more modest residences built for J.J. Walser Jr and George Barton. These earrings are inspired by stained glass in the Walser House. Details:•Solid brass •Electro-plated with a hematite finish•Hand enameled•Glass beads•Posts are plated hematite•Hangs approx. 1.50"
